cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a content delivery system over the Internet, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The system studied in the paper involves multiple co-located caches, which suggests a distributed computing architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper evaluates the performance of different content replication strategies, which involves analyzing the efficiency of algorithms used in the system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses system-level optimization of design choices, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on a Video on Demand (VoD) service, which involves multimedia content delivery.
